\dfrac{dx}{dt} = -k \exp(-kt) (a\cos(nt)+b\sin(nt)) + n \exp(-kt) (-a\sin(nt)+b\cos(nt))
\dfrac{dx}{dt}  = -kx + n \exp(-kt)(-a\sin(nt)+b\cos(nt))
\dfrac{d^2x}{dt^2} = -k - n^2 \exp(-kt)(a\cos(nt)+b\sin(nt)) - kn \exp(-kt)(-a\sin(nt)+b\cos(nt))
\dfrac{d^2x}{dt^2} = -k - n^2x - k^2x - x\dfrac{dx}{dt}
\dfrac{d^2x}{dt^2} + x\dfrac{dx}{dt} + (n^2+k^2)x + k = 0
